[[Translation:en/Manual/Construction]]
There are four transport modes in [[en/Manual/Main Page|OpenTTD]]: Rail, Rail, Sea and Air. Each has it's own construction method.


*[[File:en/Manual/Manual html m772c5b23.png]] '''[[en/Manual/Railway construction]]''' - Build [[en/Manual/Stations#train-stations|train stations]], connecting [[en/Manual/Building tracks|railway track]], and [[en/Manual/Signals]] for [[en/Manual/Trains]].
*[[File:en/Manual/Manual html ma6d6c8c.png]] '''[[en/Manual/Roadway construction]]''' - Build either [[en/Manual/Stations#bus-stations|bus stations]] and [[en/Manual/Stations#truck-stations|truck stations]], and connect them with roads for [[en/Manual/Base Set/Road Vehicles/Buses]] and/or [[en/Manual/Road vehicles]].
*[[File:en/Manual/Manual html m2cc0c4cd.png]] '''[[en/Manual/Waterway construction]]''' - Build [[en/Manual/Water Transport Tiles]] and [[en/Manual/Waypoints|bouys]] for [[en/Manual/Ships]] to follow.
*[[File:en/Manual/Manual html 1ae92703.png]] '''[[en/Manual/Airport construction]]''' - Build [[en/Manual/Airports]] and direct [[en/Manual/Aircraft|planes]] between them.

